stimulus:
Thank you for participating in this study.

Experimenter: please make sure the experiment is fullscreen (press F11).

Press B to begin.

Each trial will begin with your prediction. Do you think the five cards will contain more red cards or more black cards?

On the next slide, you will see the words “RED” and “BLACK”.

Click ← on your keyboard to choose “RED” or → to choose “BLACK”.

Press any key to continue.

RED
BLACK
+

Chosen option: RED

+

You've made your prediction. Next, the five cards will be revealed, one at a time.

If more cards in the deck are in your chosen color than the other color, you win 20 cents.

If not, you gain no money.

Press any key to see the cards revealed.
+
+
+
+
+
+

You predicted correctly!

Let's do one more practice round, this time without any instructions.

Remember, it's important for the experiment that you keep your gaze fixed on the + in the center and blink as little as possible.

Moving your eyes or blinking will add electrical noise to the data.

Press any key to start the practice trial.

RED
BLACK
+

Chosen option: RED

+
+
+
+
+
+
+

You predicted incorrectly this time.

During the experiment, sometimes one of the cards will have a white X instead of being red or black.

As soon as you see a white X, press either arrow key as quickly as possible.

On trials with a white X, you cannot win any money.

But, if you respond too slowly to the white X (more than 1.5 seconds), you will lose $1.00.

We'll show you an example now. Press any key to practice a trial with a white X.
+
+
+
+
+
+

You are ready to begin the experiment.

Please keep your gaze fixed on the + in the center and blink as little as possible.

You may move your eyes and blink whenever the + is not on the screen.

If you have any questions, please ask the experimenter now.

Once the experimenter gives you the OK, press any key to begin the real trials.
